issues.body:
For the purpose of having a model that can be used as multi-technology data model, i suggest we add a grouping called common-cable-segment-attributes and consolidate shared attributes . this groping is then used in specific containers/groupings

Suggestion: 

```
[...]
grouping common-cable-segment-attributes {
    description
      "the common attributes of passive cables";
       leaf length {
        type uint32;
        units "meter";
        description
          "Length of the cable in meter.";
      }
      leaf attenuation {
        type decimal64 {
          fraction-digits 2;
        }
        units "dB";
        description
          "The cable attenuation in dB.";
      }
      leaf serial-num {
        type string;
        description
          "The serial number of the cable.";
      }
      leaf mfg-name {
        type string;
        description
          "The name of the manufacturer of the cable.";
      }
      leaf part-number {
        type string;
        description
          "The vendor-specific part number of the cable.";
      }
      uses connected-device-ref;
  }
[...]
```
